Diepsloot township in Johannesburg is rife with poverty, unemployment — and a lot of plastic litter. But, thanks to a local NGO, community members are making eco-bricks with this waste to build classrooms.  Adel van Niekerk spoke to Diana Musara of Khensani’s Collection who is leading this endeavour. First published by GroundUp. <img data-lazy-fallback="1" style="display: none; width: 1px;" src="https://thirdpartyhits.groundup.org.za/counter/hit/dailymaverick/2022-07-12-building-classrooms-from-plastic-waste-in-diepsloot/" alt=""  />